article.headline: Troy 84, FIU 68
article.story: MIAMI -- Brandon Hazzard scored 29 points to lead Troy past Florida International 84-68 on Saturday night. The Trojans (9-7, 4-1 Sun Belt Conference) outscored the Golden Panthers 13-2 in the first 2:34 of the game and never trailed. Hazzard scored seven points, and Antywan Jones and Richard Delk each hit 3-pointers during the run. Hazzard, who shot 11 of 17 from the field and 6-for-10 from 3-point range, surpassed 1,000 career points. He is seventh on the school's all-time scoring list with 1,007 points. Delk's third 3-pointer of the first half with 11:08 remaining increased Troy's lead to 25-11. Delk finished with 17 points. Florida International (5-14, 2-4) could get no closer than 50-42 on Stephon Weaver's field goal with 15:14 remaining in the second half. Marvin Roberts led the Golden Panthers with 27 points.
